                            <comment id="21456" author="green" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2011 16:10:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately waiting with wait_osc_import_state is not as easy since we don&apos;t know the ost name to wait on due to the way we choose the ost&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21455" author="jay" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2011 15:58:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the root cause of this issue is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in sanity:test_104a it deactivated and then activated the osc import, but it failed at activation phase because there was still one RPC in flight(I don&apos;t know why because deactivation should wait all in-flight rpcs to finish). However, the test case doesn&apos;t check this case and just move forward - this is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixing this issue is easy - just wait for the import to be in FULL state by wait_osc_import_state. lfs df is not enough it doesn&apos;t return an error code even lctl activate runs into failure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
